just a little rambly explanation on tap strafing stuff!

"people need to learn how to aim now because they can't tap strafe lmaooo, get fucked"
say the people complaining about being unable to hit people as they're moving :think: funny how that works

And lessening that curve isn't the move IMO.
I say this as a rather casual player who gets put against sweatlords every single day because of apex's fucked matchmaking.

And I'm sad to see things from advanced movement taken away, and I worry that messing with something as simple as this can fuck with a lot of slide jump based movements unintentionally.
Movement is one of the major skill curves in apex with game sense and aim,

So my thoughts:
I'm more worried about them trying to remove tap strafing and ruining other movement in the process than anything, this is an issue that can affect both M+K and controller.
Movement is one of the things that sets apex apart from other games imo,
